data.description: Lovely well kept home in excellent location.  City and country views from front and back windows. Watch Fiesta Texas fireworks! There is ceramic tile in the entry, kitchen, breakfast, and utility room. The front flex space features double glass doors and could be formal dining, study or den.  Currently being used as a work out space. Family room features a wood burning fireplace with mantle and is open to the kitchen. There is also surround sound speakers and wiring. The gourmet kitchen has newer stainless appliances with smooth top stove and built in microwave. There is a movable island with floor plug underneath and there are 42" cabinets with tile backsplash. The pantry/utility room is quite spacious with extra storage. Gameroom upstairs or could be second living area with closet. Primary bedroom has dual closets and built in bookshelves. The primary ensuite features a whirlpool tub, separate tiled shower and double vanities. All the bedrooms enjoy walk in closets. Expansive deck in the back yard to enjoy the peacefull views and watch the deer. Partial wrought iron fence backs to conservation area/greenbelt. There is a peach and fig tree. There are also plumeria and garlic chive plants growing. Dog park close by and Hills and Dales pool can be joined with fee. This home has never had pets or shoes and the carpets are in great condition and have always been protected with area rugs. There is an additional side door that was added from the garage. The 30 year roof is newer. There are some upgraded fixtures throughout and a newer water softener with RO system. Make this great home yours today! Seller is offering a One Year American Home Shield Warranty.
